logentry-moderation-approve:
{{Logentry|[[Special:Log/moderation]]}}
Logentry when moderator approves ONE change.

Parameters: $1 - link to moderator, $4 - "{{msg-mw|moderation-log-diff}}", $3 - target page, $2 - plaintext name of moderator (for GENDER).

logentry-moderation-approveall:
{{Logentry|[[Special:Log/moderation]]}}
Logentry when moderator approves ALL changes of ONE author.

Parameters: $1 - link to moderator, $4 - number of approved edits, $3 - link to author, $2 - plaintext name of moderator (for GENDER).

logentry-moderation-approve-move:
{{Logentry|[[Special:Log/moderation]]}}
Logentry when moderator approves suggestion to rename  the page.

Parameters: $1 - link to moderator, $3 - old title of the article, $4 - new title of the article, $5 - link to user who suggested the move, $2 - plaintext name of moderator (for GENDER).

logentry-moderation-block:
{{Logentry|[[Special:Log/moderation]]}}
Logentry when moderator marks someone as spammer.

Parameters: $1 - link to moderator, $3 - affected user, $2 - plaintext name of moderator (for GENDER).

logentry-moderation-merge:
{{Logentry|[[Special:Log/moderation]]}}
Logentry when moderator manually resolves an edit conflict.

Parameters: $1 - link to moderator, $3 - affected page, $4 - "{{msg-mw|moderation-log-change}}", $5 - "{{msg-mw|moderation-log-diff}}", $2 - plaintext name of moderator (for GENDER).

logentry-moderation-reject:
{{Logentry|[[Special:Log/moderation]]}}
Logentry when moderator rejects ONE change.

Parameters: $1 - link to moderator, $3 - link to author, $4 - "{{msg-mw|moderation-log-change}}", $2 - plaintext name of moderator (for GENDER).

logentry-moderation-rejectall:
{{Logentry|[[Special:Log/moderation]]}}
Logentry when moderator rejects ALL changes of ONE author.

Parameters: $1 - link to moderator, $3 - link to author, $4 - number of edits, $2 - plaintext name of moderator (for GENDER).

logentry-moderation-unblock:
{{Logentry|[[Special:Log/moderation]]}}
Logentry when moderator unmarks someone as spammer.

Parameters: $1 - link to moderator, $3 - affected user, $2 - plaintext name of moderator (for GENDER).
